From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 16:39:58 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rockchip: enter rockusb loader mode on BOOT_LOADER reboot
 flag

setup_boot_mode() reads the Rockchip reboot-mode register and dispatches
BOOT_FASTBOOT and BOOT_UMS, but ignores BOOT_LOADER (0x5242C301) -- the
value the kernel's syscon-reboot-mode writes for "reboot loader". Handle
it by arming preboot to run the rockusb gadget, so a board can re-enter
USB flash (loader) mode from a running Linux with no physical button and
no maskrom, mirroring the vendor loader's convenience.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
index 55e94566..1563b1bd 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
@@ -97,6 +97,10 @@ int setup_boot_mode(void)
 	writel(BOOT_NORMAL, reg);
 
 	switch (boot_mode) {
+	case BOOT_LOADER:
+		debug("%s: enter rockusb!\n", __func__);
+		env_set("preboot", "setenv preboot; rockusb 0 mmc 0");
+		break;
 	case BOOT_FASTBOOT:
 		debug("%s: enter fastboot!\n", __func__);
 		env_set("preboot", "setenv preboot; fastboot usb 0");
